,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/02\/06\/eating-dinner-maghrib-prayer\/","url_meta":{"origin":29356,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Prayer: Eating dinner before Maghrib prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 6, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIf dinner is presented close to the time of prayer, begin eating before you perform sunset prayer and do not need to rush away from your dinner.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 640, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 558 Grade:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17993,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/02\/02\/bad-smell-offends-angels\/","url_meta":{"origin":29356,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Angels: Whatever offends people also offends angels","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 2, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir ibn Abdullah reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever eats onions, garlic, or leeks should not approach our mosque, for the angels are offended by whatever offends the children of Adam.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 564 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u062c\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650\u0631\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15275,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/22\/invitation-dua-for-host\/","url_meta":{"origin":29356,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Invitations: Accept invites, supplicate for host","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 22, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIf one of you is invited for a meal, let him respond. If he is fasting, let him pray for the host. If he is not fasting, let him eat.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1431 Grade: Sahih\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":23629,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/08\/23\/waiting-for-prayer\/","url_meta":{"origin":29356,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Salat: You are in prayer even as you wait for it","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 23, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cOne of you continues to be in prayer as long as the prayer occupies him, and nothing stops him from returning to his family but prayer.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 649 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15104,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/16\/walk-in-prayer\/","url_meta":{"origin":29356,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Salah: When walking to prayer, you are in prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 16, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen the prayer is established, do not come to it running, but rather come to it walking. You must be calm, for you may pray it if you reach it in time. If you miss anything\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28106,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/23\/allah-has-waived-fasting-half-of-prayer\/","url_meta":{"origin":29356,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Travel: Allah has waived fasting, half of prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 23, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Amr ibn Umayyah reported: I came to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, from a journey and he said, \u201cStay to eat, O Abu Umayyah.\u201d I said, \u201cIndeed, I am fasting.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cCome close to me and I will tell you about the traveler.\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/29356","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"aut